Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Close to nearby dining and retail

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer for sale 118 Hobart Street, Mount Hawthorn.

The property comprises 180sqm* of building area situated on a rectangular shaped allotment of 534sqm*, situated slightly setback from Scarborough Beach road and in close proximity to Mount Hawthorn’s thriving retail, dining and restaurant precinct.

Zoned ‘District Centre’ under the City of Vincent’s Local Planning Scheme No. 2, permitted uses include liquor store, restaurant/café and shop.

The property is offered with a medium-term leaseback via offers to purchase invited, closing Wednesday 9th October 2019 at 4pm.

For further details or to request the information memorandum, please contact the exclusive selling agents CBRE.

• Prime 232sqm* retail space with flexibility to combine as one or split into two tenancies
• 582sqm* site with extensive Oxford St frontage
• Zoned 'Commercial' - City of Vincent
• Valuable rear lane access and car parking
• Potential to develop up to 4* levels (STCA)
• Pending re-zoning to District Centre
• Offered with vacant possession
• Cosmopolitan retail, service and cafe precinct

Great opportunity for restaurant, retail, cafe, office, mixed use and residential in the heart of the highly sought after Mount Hawthorn.

Offers to Purchase Invited closing Thursday 17th March 2016 at 2.00pm (AWST)
